Package com.blockwithme.util.shared

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AsDouble
    AsDouble can be implemented by objects that can be represented as a primitive double.
    AsLong
    AsLong can be implemented by objects that can be represented as a primitive long.
    FuzzyEvaluator<E>
    FuzzyEvaluator is implemented by some object that can "evaluate" the fuzzy level of some other object.
    FuzzySource
    FuzzSource is implemented by some object that can "evaluate" themselves to a fuzzy level.
    RandomEventSource
    RandomEventSource is implemented by some object that can generate "random events", where the range is between 0 inclusive and 1 exclusive.
    Registry<K,V>
    Registry is a generic registry.
    Validator<E>
    Validates some values.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Any
    Smallest possible mutable class that could contain anything, without requiring "boxing" of primitive values (except long!).
    AnyArray
    Smallest possible mutable class that could contain a bunch of anything, without requiring "boxing" of primitive values (except long!).
    DefaultApplication
    The default Application implementation.
    DefaultTimeSource
    Default implementation of TimeSource.
    DoubleMiniMap
    DoubleMiniMap contains static methods, to simulate a map of double (or any other non-long primitive type) on a small single array.
    ExactTypeValidator<E>
    ExactTypeValidator validates that the values are of the exact given type.
    Footprint
    Helper class to compute the approximate memory footprint of an object.
    MiniMap
    MiniMap contains static methods, to simulate a map of properties on a small single array.
    MurmurHash
    File copied from http://d3s.mff.cuni.cz/~holub/sw/javamurmurhash/MurmurHash.java Murmur hash 2.0.
    Preconditions
    Some non-Xtend compatible validation code
    RegistryImpl<K,V>
    Registry is a generic registry.
    Statics
    This class should be used to eliminate all non-primitive static members.
    SuperclassTypeValidator<E>
    SuperclassTypeValidator validates that the values are not null and of the given type, or a subtype.
    Validators
    Some pre-defined validators.
